Health Minister Zweli Khize says it's important that people get moral support before they are admitted to hospital. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has stressed the importance of moral support before being admitted to hospital. Mkhize says a lot of people are overwhelmed with anxiety in dealing with COVID-19. READ: Mkhize: Gauteng ahead of COVID-19 surge "When people get nervous they need someone to talk to, and it doesn't just happen to non-medical staff, even for our own staff has that problem. "So this why we need support for psychological counselling," he said. The health minister was visiting the Eastern Cape to assess the province's interventions amid COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.